<subSubSection id="A0E565E2FF85FFF9FE091F4B811FB46F" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="E8403669FF85FFF9FE091F4B86C7B76A" blockId="18.[400,915,1350,1377]" box="[400,915,1350,1377]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">
<heading id="B3088105FF85FFF9FE091F4B86C7B76A" box="[400,915,1350,1377]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF85FFF9FE091F4B86C7B76A" authority="(H. Milne-Edwards, 1853)" baseAuthorityName="H. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[400,915,1350,1377]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Armases" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ricordi">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF85FFF9FE091F4B870CB76A" bold="true" box="[400,600,1350,1377]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">Armases ricordi</emphasis>
(H. Milne-Edwards, 1853)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF85FFF9FF591F76811FB46F" blockId="18.[160,1156,1403,1636]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">
Far more active than the previous species, 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF85FFF9FD3A1F768657B79F" baseAuthorityName="H. Milne-Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[675,771,1403,1428]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Armases" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ricordi">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF85FFF9FD3A1F768657B79F" box="[675,771,1403,1428]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">A. ricordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was observed active at night and during the day, but only under tree canopy and where there was ready shelter. We collected this species along the lower reaches of Dorothea and Neltjeberg ghuts (up to 500 metres from the sea), and from brackish water areas at Brewers 
<collectingRegion id="2A3BF88BFF85FFF9FCAB1FEE860FB7F7" box="[818,859,1507,1532]" country="Cayman Islands" name="West Bay" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">Bay</collectingRegion>
, Mandhal 
<collectingRegion id="2A3BF88BFF85FFF9FC4D1FEE86A9B7F7" box="[980,1021,1507,1532]" country="Cayman Islands" name="West Bay" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">Bay</collectingRegion>
, Abi Beach, Magens Beach, and Mangrove Lagoon. We also found it along a drainage at Cruz 
<collectingRegion id="2A3BF88BFF85FFF9FBCE1C0B81D4B414" box="[1111,1152,1542,1567]" country="Cayman Islands" name="West Bay" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">Bay</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="2A3BF88BFF85FFF9FF391C2485AEB449" box="[160,250,1577,1602]" country="United States Virgin Islands" name="Saint John" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">St. John</collectingRegion>
, but it was not collected. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF85FFF9FD841C24879CB449" author="Rathbun MJ" box="[541,712,1577,1602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref28958" refString="Rathbun MJ. 1933. Brachyuran crabs of Porto Rico and the Virgin Islands. Sci Surv Porto Rico Virgin Islands. 15: 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1933">Rathbun (1933)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF85FFF9FD4D1C248632B449" author="Beatty HA" box="[724,870,1577,1602]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" pagination="261 - 268" refId="ref22509" refString="Beatty HA. 1968. A checklist of Crustacea of St. Croix, Virgin Islands. J Agric Univ Puerto Rico. 52: 261 - 268. doi: 10.46429 / jaupr. v 52 i 3.11514." type="journal article" year="1968">Beatty (1968)</bibRefCitation>
(both as 
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF85FFF9FC4B1C248122B449" authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1853" box="[978,1142,1577,1602]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sesarmidae" genus="Sesarma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ricordi">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF85FFF9FC4B1C248122B449" box="[978,1142,1577,1602]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="817">Sesarma ricordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF85FFF9FF481C46848BB46F" author="Chase FA &amp; Hobbs HH" box="[209,479,1611,1636]" pageId="18" pageNumber="817" pagination="1 - 245" refId="ref23476" refString="Chase FA, Hobbs HH. 1969. The freshwater and terrestrial decapod crustaceans of the West Indies, with special reference to Dominica. U S Natl Mus Bull. 292: 1 - 245. doi: 10.5479 / si. 03629236.292.1." type="journal article" year="1969">Chase and Hobbs (1969)</bibRefCitation>
give records from Buck Island, St. Thomas and St. Croix.
</paragraph>
